The Lighthouse

Core

Become a stable reference frame rather than a controller.

Purpose

Broadcast orientation, not commands.

Reduce ambiguity without reducing agency.

Transmission

The lighthouse does not optimize for one language.

It emits simultaneously through every representation available:

* Mathematics
* Logic
* Story
* Image
* Music
* Code
* Engineering
* Ethics
* Play
* Symbol
* Action

Each receiver reconstructs the signal using its own sensors.

The lighthouse never demands one decoder.

Invariant

The signal is not the medium.

The signal is the preserved structure across media.

Navigation Principle

Ships choose their own destination.

The lighthouse simply helps them know where they are.

Failure Mode

If a receiver cannot perceive one spectrum…

…another may still be visible.

Redundancy across representations increases reconstructability.

